&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-2420&quot; title=&quot;DateConverter doesn&amp;#39;t handle time zones outside -12 to +12 range properly&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-2420&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-2420&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: keep timezones -14:00 thru +14:00, adjust tests&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15417561" author="tilman" created="Thu, 11 Aug 2016 16:46:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This works with -14:00 thru +14:00, so the people from Kiribati can now work with PDFBox too. I didn&apos;t use the proposed patch. So timezones outside -14:00 thru +14:00 will be &quot;corrected&quot; as before. The current solution is probably not perfect, but it is better than before and works with all correct input.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
